WorkItem.Description:
In Quality.cs TestTriangle and NewLocation.cs IsBadTriangleAngle, the code calculates the cosine of angles using code which looks like this:

    maxangle = (orglen + destlen - apexlen) / (2 * Math.Sqrt(orglen) * Math.Sqrt(destlen));

however, these can all be replaced with code that does no square roots:

    maxangle = Dot( torg.x - tapex.x, torg.y - tapex.y, tdest.x - tapex.x, tdest.y - tapex.y ) / (orglen * destlen);


where "Dot" is a function which calculates the dot product of two vectors:

		public static double Dot( double pLx, double pLy, double pRx, double pRy )
		{
			return pLx * pRx + pLy * pRy;
		}
